<body> 
 <pb n="1" id="Tw8402171">  
<div1 type="letter"> 
<opener> 
<seg> 
<figure entity="T840217a"> 
<figDesc>Papers of Mark Twain,  AL 1884 Feb 17; 
Mark Twain to Augustin Daly; 
image of page one of the manuscript. 
</figDesc> 
</figure> 
</seg> 
<dateline> 
<date n="1884-02-17"><abbr expan="February">Feb.</abbr> 17/84.</date></dateline> 
<salute>Dear Mr. Daly &mdash </salute> 
</opener> 
 
<p>I have been <orig reg="dramatizing">dra- <lb> 
matizing</orig> a book of<lb> 
mine ("The Adventures <lb> 
of Tom Sawyer") &amp; I <lb> 
wonder if you would <lb> 
like to take a look at <lb> 
the result, with an eye <lb> 
to business?  If so, <lb> 
I will <add place="supralinear">bring</add> the play down when I <lb> 
return to New York <del>Wednesday</del> <add place="supralinear">Thursday</add>.</p> 
 
<closer> 
<salute><abbr expan="Yours">Yr</abbr> truly<lb></salute> 
<signed>Mark Twain</signed> 
</closer> 
</div1> 
   
</body> 
